# Lean — efficient development lifecycle (iPix)

**Orchestrator rule.** Delegates detail to sibling rules — do not duplicate their full text here.

| Rule / skill | Role |
|--------------|------|
| `graphify.mdc` | Query graph before broad source reads |
| `ponytail.mdc` | Smallest safe change ladder during implementation |
| `task-naming.mdc` | **IPI-NNN · SPEC — Title** in user-facing text |
| `infisical.mdc` | `infisical run --env=dev --` for secrets |
| `.claude/skills/worktrees/` | Worktree create, health, cleanup |
| `.claude/skills/pr-workflow/` | Verify matrix, PR shape, one concern per PR |
| `.claude/skills/ipix-task-lifecycle/` | Five-phase IPI delivery hub |

**Hard gates (never override):** never push to `main`; one concern per PR **and** per commit; build in `app/` not retiring `src/`; remote-only Supabase; no client AI keys.

## Operating modes

Set explicitly (`lean-strict`, `lean-relaxed`) or default to **lean-standard**.

| Mode | When | Worktree | Tests | Plan |
|------|------|----------|-------|------|
| **lean-relaxed** | Typo, copy, single-file fix, docs-only | Skip if clean tree + one file | Focused test or lint only | Mental checklist OK |
| **lean-standard** | Default IPI feature/fix | Required for multi-file / multi-step | Verify matrix rows for touched paths | Short written plan |
| **lean-strict** | Migrations, RLS, auth, payments, Mastra/agents, Cloudflare deploy | Always | Full matrix + build when applicable + manual probes | Plan + rollback notes |

## Decision ladder (reuse → create)

Apply **after** graphify discovery and **during** implementation (see `ponytail.mdc` for full ladder):

```text
1. Does this need to exist? (YAGNI)
2. Does it already exist in this repo?
3. Can existing code be extended safely?
4. Stdlib / native platform?
5. Installed dependency (no new package)?
6. Only then: minimum new code
```

| Decision | Choose when | Avoid when |
|----------|-------------|------------|
| **Reuse** | Same behavior, same boundary | Hidden coupling or wrong abstraction level |
| **Extend** | One call site, clear owner module | File already overloaded |
| **New code** | No safe extension point | "Might need later" |
| **New dependency** | Clear gap, no stdlib/existing lib | One function wrapper |
| **Refactor** | Blocks correct minimal fix; evidence in diff | Drive-by cleanup |
| **Worktree** | Multi-step task or dirty main tree | One-line fix on clean branch |
| **Focused tests** | Every commit during implementation | Full suite on every save |
| **Full suite / build** | Routes, env, middleware, pre-PR | Docs-only change |
| **Open PR** | Branch pushed, local verify green | Mixed concerns still in diff |
| **Remove worktree** | PR merged, branch merged, tree clean | Any uncertainty on uncommitted work |

## Lifecycle (entry → action → verify → exit)

### 1. Understand

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | New task, user request, or Linear issue |
| **Do** | Read issue/spec (`docs/linear/issues/IPI-*.md`), AC, dependencies; name task per `task-naming.mdc`; list completion checklist and non-goals |
| **Verify** | Expected outcome + boundaries are unambiguous |
| **Exit** | Checklist written; blockers flagged; no edits yet |

### 2. Discover

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Task boundary understood |
| **Do** | `graphify query/explain/path`; `rg` for exact symbols; trace real execution path; confirm partial/full existing impl |
| **Verify** | Reuse candidates identified or "net-new" justified |
| **Exit** | Know which files will likely change |

```bash
graphify query "<feature>"
graphify explain "<symbol>"
graphify path "<A>" "<B>"
rg -l "<exactSymbol>" app/ supabase/
```

### 3. Plan

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Discovery complete |
| **Do** | Short plan: files, reuse, tests, risks/trust boundaries, non-goals, verify commands |
| **Verify** | Plan fits task size (≤10 bullets for small tasks) |
| **Exit** | Plan approved or implicit for trivial fixes |

### 4. Isolate (worktree)

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Multi-file task, parallel work, or **lean-standard+** |
| **Do** | `npm run worktree:audit`; create or reuse `../wt-ipi-<id>-<slug>`; branch `ipi/<id>-<slug>`; copy env via `.worktreeinclude` |
| **Verify** | `node scripts/worktree-health.mjs` passes in existing wt |
| **Exit** | Correct branch, clean or intentional dirty state |

```bash
npm run worktree:audit
npm run worktree:add -- IPI-NNN short-name
node scripts/worktree-health.mjs
git branch --show-current   # expect ipi/NNN-short-name
```

**Skip worktree** only in **lean-relaxed** on a clean tree with a single-file change.

### 5. Implement

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Plan + isolation ready |
| **Do** | Smallest change; reuse APIs; one concern; `ponytail:` for deferred shortcuts; no drive-by refactors |
| **Verify** | AC satisfied; diff stays scoped |
| **Exit** | Code complete; ready for progressive test |

### 6. Test (progressive)

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Behavior changed |
| **Do** | Ladder: focused test → feature tests → typecheck → lint → integration → E2E → full suite when justified |
| **Verify** | New/changed behavior covered; bug repro fails before fix; no weakened tests |
| **Exit** | Relevant verify matrix rows green |

**iPix commands (pick by touched path):**

```bash
# app/ (canonical)
cd app && npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm test
cd app && npm run build    # routes, config, env, middleware

# Supabase
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify-rls
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify-edge      # edge functions
infisical run --env=dev -- npm run supabase:verify-brand-intelligence

# Secrets-wrapped dev
cd app && infisical run --env=dev -- npm run dev
```

Domain checks: **Supabase** — migrations order, RLS, RPC; **Cloudflare** — bindings, wrangler, runtime; **Mastra** — agent IDs sync, `getMastra()` in handlers only, HITL/schemas.

### 7. Diff review (pre-commit)

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Tests green for scope |
| **Do** | `git status`, `git diff`; remove debug noise, secrets, accidental formatting; confirm no mixed concerns |
| **Verify** | Only intended files; AC met |
| **Exit** | Staged set matches one commit concern |

```bash
git status --short
git diff --stat
git diff
```

### 8. Commit

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Diff reviewed |
| **Do** | One logical commit; conventional message with task id |
| **Verify** | No `.env*`, artifacts, or unrelated paths |
| **Exit** | Commit on task branch |

```text
fix(ipi-397): enforce booking agent draft-only guard
feat(ipi-476): add planner output schema validation
```

### 9. Pull request

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Commit(s) ready; branch pushed |
| **Do** | Rebase if needed; `gh pr create`; body: problem, cause, solution, files, tests, security/data impact, limitations, rollback, linked issue |
| **Verify** | Local matrix green; **one concern**; docs-only vs code split |
| **Exit** | PR open, CI running |

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create --title "IPI-NNN · SPEC — Plain English title" --body "..."
```

Pre-push hook runs typecheck + tests — fix root cause if it fails; never `--no-verify` except docs-only without app code.

### 10. CI & review

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | PR open |
| **Do** | Fix CI root cause; address valid review; reject scope creep with reason; re-run affected tests first |
| **Verify** | Required checks green; threads resolved |
| **Exit** | Merge-ready |

```bash
gh run list --limit 5
gh run view <id> --log-failed
```

### 11. Merge

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | Reviews + CI pass |
| **Do** | Confirm migrations/deploy deps; squash merge unless policy says otherwise |
| **Verify** | No open blocking threads |
| **Exit** | On `main` via merge |

### 12. Cleanup

| | |
|---|---|
| **Enter** | PR merged |
| **Do** | Confirm merge; remove worktree safely; prune branches; refresh graph if large merge |
| **Verify** | No lost uncommitted work |
| **Exit** | Issue updated; follow-ups filed separately |

**Before `git worktree remove` — all must be yes or inspected:**

```text
Clean? Committed? Pushed? PR merged? Branch merged? Env backed up? No unique untracked files?
```

```bash
git worktree list
git branch --merged main
git worktree remove ../wt-ipi-NNN-slug   # never -f unless inspected
git branch -d ipi/NNN-slug
git worktree prune
graphify update .   # after significant structural merge
```

## Worktree hygiene

- One task per worktree; no duplicate wt for same issue
- Inspect regularly: `npm run worktree:audit`, `git worktree list`
- Never delete uncertain trees — inspect `git status` inside first

## Context & token efficiency

- **Graphify before grep storms** — one query beats reading 10 files
- **Targeted reads** — open symbols/ranges from graph results, not whole directories
- **Summarize** before loading more files
- **Stop** when evidence suffices
- **No regenerate** — skip `supabase:types`, graph rebuild, etc. when inputs unchanged
- **Follow-ups** → new Linear issues, not hidden TODOs
- **Claim done only with evidence** — test output, probe, or inspection

## Task lifecycle checklist

Copy for every **lean-standard+** task:

```text
[ ] Issue + AC understood          [ ] Graphify discovery done
[ ] Lean plan (files, reuse, tests) [ ] Worktree + branch correct
[ ] worktree-health passed          [ ] Smallest safe implementation
[ ] Progressive tests green         [ ] Diff review (no secrets/mix)
[ ] Focused commit(s)               [ ] PR opened (one concern)
[ ] CI green                        [ ] Merged
[ ] Worktree removed safely         [ ] Issue closed / follow-ups filed
```

## Decision flow (summary)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Task received] --> B{Boundary clear?}
  B -->|no| B1[Clarify AC + non-goals]
  B -->|yes| C[graphify query + rg]
  C --> D{Exists already?}
  D -->|yes| E[Reuse or extend]
  D -->|no| F{Need new code?}
  F --> G[Ponytail ladder]
  E --> H{Multi-file or dirty tree?}
  G --> H
  H -->|yes| I[worktree + ipi branch]
  H -->|no| J[Implement on current branch]
  I --> K[Implement smallest change]
  J --> K
  K --> L[Progressive tests]
  L --> M{Verify matrix green?}
  M -->|no| K
  M -->|yes| N[Diff review + commit]
  N --> O[PR + CI]
  O --> P{Merged?}
  P -->|yes| Q[Safe worktree cleanup]
```

